Set up an S3 bucket in AWS, ensuring the name is globally unique. Upload your static website files (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, etc.) to this bucket. Enable static website hosting in the S3 bucket properties and configure the documents. Apply the necessary bucket policy to make your site publicly accessible. Also, enable versioning on the bucket to maintain previous versions of your website files. 

